HEADWORD: Ularburong
<hw>U*lar"bu*rong</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the native
Malay name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large East Indian nocturnal
tree snake (<spn>Dipsas dendrophila</spn>). It is not
venomous.</def>⟦br⟧
